latestIgtvVideos.title: Create A Safe Space For Yourself with @baring.soul !✨🤍
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It’s a hard time for everyone during this time of the pandemic and often times we forget to take care of ourselves. In this live session we did a live grounding and breath work, we discussed tools to manage anxiousness, what is active meditation and also self care! 🌸
Taking out 5mins for yourself everyday to do something that makes you feel safe and brings you joy can help you thrive in so many ways and when you take care of yourself, you are able to do more for others around you. 🤗
.
Let go of any expectations that you have from yourself, any pressure you are putting on yourself and join us in this session to check-in with yourself ✨🤍
.
.
.
.

Harmless? Maybe Not ⬇️

It’s the small things that add up to making you start doubting yourself and losing your confidence.
Hiding under clothes, avoiding opportunities, avoiding being seen or voicing your opinions, apologising for trivial things, etc. These might seem small and harmless but they do greater damage if not corrected!

Making yourself small and hiding your potential is just holding yourself back and missing out on the time you could be living you best most happy life! It is a disservice to WHO YOU ARE MEANT TO BE!! 

I know, I know, easier said than done! I know it’s difficult to navigate your emotions and thoughts by yourself without a roadmap and hence I create the BOLD method, that is 3 phase step by step framework that helps you go from struggling with showing up confidently to actually becoming your most confident self! 🤩

It’s a proven method that helped me and my clients to let go of all our inhibitions and make BOLD-er moves in life 😮‍💨

➡️ Want to know more? Follow and Comment “CONFIDENCE” and I’ll send you the details 💜

I won’t lie… coming back to social media after feeling disconnected is HARD. But here’s the truth—I’m rebranding, not just my content, but my mindset. ✨

2024 was a year full of surprises and curveballs and it has taken me some time to figure things out, whether it was my creative block, content burnout or diagnosis of Lipedema - understanding, navigating and treating it has been a whole other journey till now 😅

I want to share my journey with you. The highs, the lows, the lessons, and the raw moments in between. I am ready to step into this next chapter of my life and I look forward to sharing it with you. 💜

Once again, those who’ve stuck around, I am so grateful for you and I hope you will support me moving forward too because this is just the beginning of this new era 🥰

.
.
